191 226 class Hive(Place):
192 227 """The Place from which the Bees launch their assault.
193 228
194 229 assault_plan -- An AssaultPlan; when & where bees enter the colony.
195 230 """
196 231
197 232 def __init__(self, assault_plan):
198 233 self.name = 'Hive'
199 234 self.assault_plan = assault_plan
200 235 self.bees = []
201 236 for bee in assault_plan.all_bees:
202 237 self.add_insect(bee)
203 238 # The following attributes are always None for a Hive
204 239 self.entrance = None
205 240 self.ant = None
206 241 self.exit = None
207 242
208 243 def strategy(self, colony):
209 244 exits = [p for p in colony.places.values() if p.entrance is self]
210 245 for bee in self.assault_plan.get(colony.time, []):
211 246 bee.move_to(random.choice(exits))

214 249 class AntColony:
215 250 """An ant collective that manages global game state and simulates time.
216 251
217 252 Attributes:
218 253 time -- elapsed time
219 254 food -- the colony's available food total
220 255 queen -- the place where the queen resides
221 256 places -- A list of all places in the colony (including a Hive)
222 257 bee_entrances -- A list of places that bees can enter
223 258 """
224 259
225 260 def __init__(self, strategy, hive, ant_types, create_places, food=2):
226 261 """Create an AntColony for simulating a game.
227 262
228 263 Arguments:
229 264 strategy -- a function to deploy ants to places
230 265 hive -- a Hive full of bees
231 266 ant_types -- a list of ant constructors
232 267 create_places -- a function that creates the set of places
233 268 """
234 269 self.time = 0
235 270 self.food = food
236 271 self.strategy = strategy
237 272 self.hive = hive
238 273 self.ant_types = OrderedDict((a.name, a) for a in ant_types)
239 274 self.configure(hive, create_places)
240 275
241 276 def configure(self, hive, create_places):
242 277 """Configure the places in the colony."""
243 278 self.queen = Place('AntQueen')
244 279 self.places = OrderedDict()
245 280 self.bee_entrances = []
246 281 def register_place(place, is_bee_entrance):
247 282 self.places[place.name] = place
248 283 if is_bee_entrance:
249 284 place.entrance = hive
250 285 self.bee_entrances.append(place)
251 286 register_place(self.hive, False)
252 287 create_places(self.queen, register_place)
253 288
254 289 def simulate(self):
255 290 """Simulate an attack on the ant colony (i.e., play the game)."""
256 291 while len(self.queen.bees) == 0 and len(self.bees) > 0:
257 292 self.hive.strategy(self) # Bees invade
258 293 self.strategy(self) # Ants deploy
259 294 for ant in self.ants: # Ants take actions
260 295 if ant.armor > 0:
261 296 ant.action(self)
262 297 for bee in self.bees: # Bees take actions
263 298 if bee.armor > 0:
264 299 bee.action(self)
265 300 self.time += 1
266 301 if len(self.queen.bees) > 0:
267 302 print('The ant queen has perished. Please try again.')
268 303 else:
269 304 print('All bees are vanquished. You win!')
270 305
271 306 def deploy_ant(self, place_name, ant_type_name):
272 307 """Place an ant if enough food is available.
273 308
274 309 This method is called by the current strategy to deploy ants.
275 310 """
276 311 constructor = self.ant_types[ant_type_name]
277 312 if self.food < constructor.food_cost:
278 313 print('Not enough food remains to place ' + ant_type_name)
279 314 else:
280 315 self.places[place_name].add_insect(constructor())
281 316 self.food -= constructor.food_cost
282 317
283 318 def remove_ant(self, place_name):
284 319 """Remove an Ant from the Colony."""
285 320 place = self.places[place_name]
286 321 if place.ant is not None:
287 322 place.remove_insect(place.ant)
288 323
289 324 @property
290 325 def ants(self):
291 326 return [p.ant for p in self.places.values() if p.ant is not None]
292 327
293 328 @property
294 329 def bees(self):
295 330 return [b for p in self.places.values() for b in p.bees]
296 331
297 332 @property
298 333 def insects(self):
299 334 return self.ants + self.bees
300 335
301 336 def __str__(self):
302 337 status = ' (Food: {0}, Time: {1})'.format(self.food, self.time)
303 338 return str([str(i) for i in self.ants + self.bees]) + status

306 341 def ant_types():
307 342 """Return a list of all implemented Ant classes."""
308 343 all_ant_types = []
309 344 new_types = [Ant]
310 345 while new_types:
311 346 new_types = [t for c in new_types for t in c.__subclasses__()]
312 347 all_ant_types.extend(new_types)
313 348 return [t for t in all_ant_types if t.implemented]

358 393 def wet_layout(queen, register_place, length=8, tunnels=3, moat_frequency=3):
359 394 """Register a mix of wet and and dry places."""
360 395 for tunnel in range(tunnels):
361 396 exit = queen
362 397 for step in range(length):
363 398 if moat_frequency != 0 and (step + 1) % moat_frequency == 0:
364 399 exit = Water('water_{0}_{1}'.format(tunnel, step), exit)
365 400 else:
366 401 exit = Place('tunnel_{0}_{1}'.format(tunnel, step), exit)
367 402 register_place(exit, step == length - 1)
368 403
369 404 def dry_layout(queen, register_place, length=8, tunnels=3):
370 405 """Register dry tunnels."""
371 406 wet_layout(queen, register_place, length, tunnels, 0)
372 407
373 408 def test_layout(queen, register_place, length=8):
374 409 """Register a single dry tunnel."""
375 410 dry_layout(queen, register_place, length, 1)

383 418 class AssaultPlan(dict):
384 419 """The Bees' plan of attack for the Colony. Attacks come in timed waves.
385 420
386 421 An AssaultPlan is a dictionary from times (int) to waves (list of Bees).
387 422
388 423 >>> AssaultPlan().add_wave(4, 2)
389 424 {4: [Bee(3, None), Bee(3, None)]}
390 425 """
391 426
392 427 def __init__(self, bee_armor=3):
393 428 self.bee_armor = bee_armor
394 429
395 430 def add_wave(self, time, count):
396 431 """Add a wave at time with count Bees that have the specified armor."""
397 432 bees = [Bee(self.bee_armor) for _ in range(count)]
398 433 self.setdefault(time, []).extend(bees)
399 434 return self
400 435
401 436 @property
402 437 def all_bees(self):
403 438 """Place all Bees in the hive and return the list of Bees."""
404 439 return [bee for wave in self.values() for bee in wave]
405 440
406 441 def make_test_assault_plan():
407 442 return AssaultPlan().add_wave(2, 1).add_wave(3, 1)
408 443
409 444 def make_full_assault_plan():
410 445 plan = AssaultPlan().add_wave(2, 1)
411 446 for time in range(3, 15, 2):
412 447 plan.add_wave(time, 1)
413 448 return plan.add_wave(15, 8)
414 449
415 450 def make_insane_assault_plan():
416 451 plan = AssaultPlan(4).add_wave(1, 2)
417 452 for time in range(3, 15):
418 453 plan.add_wave(time, 1)
419 454 return plan.add_wave(15, 20)
